@@ -0,0 +1,110 @@
+# Hardening Wave 2 — Request Boundaries and Mutation Safety
+
+Date: 2026-06-19
+
+This pass continues the stabilization work from the first hardened archive. The focus is API mutation safety: every high-traffic route should reject malformed input at the HTTP boundary before the value can reach Prisma, queues, SMTP/IMAP, Stripe, or discovery providers.
+
+## What changed
+
+### Central validation helpers
+
+- Improved `apps/api/src/lib/validate.ts` error messages so object-level refinements no longer return a leading empty path.
+- Made `workspaceIdField` trim and enforce a maximum length.
+- Added a shared `idField` for route schemas that accept arrays of IDs.
+
+### Leads
+
+Converted these routes to central Zod validation:
+
+- `POST /api/leads`
+- `POST /api/leads/import`
+- `PATCH /api/leads/:id`
+- `POST /api/leads/bulk-delete`
+- `POST /api/leads/bulk-stage`
+- `POST /api/leads/bulk-assign`
+- `PATCH /api/leads/:id/drafts/:draftId`
+
+Important behavior change: lead imports now reject malformed rows instead of silently dropping rows with missing `businessName`. This is safer for production because users see bad input immediately instead of discovering missing leads later.
+
+### Campaigns
+
+Converted campaign updates and sends to central validation:
+
+- `PATCH /api/campaigns/:id`
+- `POST /api/campaigns/:id/send`
+
+`leadIds` are now validated as strings before they can reach Prisma. The send payload is also pinned to the shared `SendCampaignRequest` contract.
+
+### Billing
+
+Converted checkout and portal payloads to central validation:
+
+- `POST /api/billing/checkout`
+- `POST /api/billing/portal`
+
+Checkout still resolves the Stripe price server-side from the safe plan enum only.
+
+### Mailbox
+
+Converted mailbox mutation payloads to central validation:
+
+- `POST /api/mailbox/send-test`
+- `POST /api/mailbox/sync`
+
+Also added domain syntax validation to `GET /api/mailbox/check-domain` before DNS resolution.
+
+### Workspaces
+
+Converted user-facing workspace mutations to central validation:
+
+- `POST /api/workspaces`
+- `POST /api/workspaces/:id/members`
+- `POST /api/workspaces/:id/invites`
+- `PUT /api/workspaces/:id/email-config`
+- `PUT /api/workspaces/:id/icp`
+- `POST /api/workspaces/:id/seed`
+
+Email configuration validation remains compatible with common form behavior: blank host/user/password/port fields normalize to `null`, and numeric port strings are accepted.
+
+### Prospects
+
+Converted core prospect mutation routes to central validation:
+
+- `POST /api/prospects`
+- `PATCH /api/prospects/:id`
+- `POST /api/prospects/:id/outcome`
+
+Also tightened `POST /api/prospects/discover` constraints for list sizes, employee ranges, source length, and discovery limit.
+
+### Tests
+
+Updated `tests/routes-leads.test.ts` to cover the new safer import behavior and reject non-string IDs before Prisma calls are made.
+
+## Validation performed
+
+Passed:
+
+```bash
+npm run check:boundaries
+```
+
+Could not complete without dependencies installed:
+
+```bash
+npm run typecheck
+npm test
+```
+
+The archive does not include `node_modules`, so TypeScript stops at the missing Node type definitions before checking the modified API files.
+
+## Recommended next pass
+
+1. Run `npm ci && npm run typecheck && npm test` in a normal developer environment.
+2. Finish converting the remaining long-tail mutation routes:
+   - `jobs.ts`
+   - `signals.ts`
+   - `outcomes.ts`
+   - `ingest.ts`
+   - remaining intent sub-actions in `prospects.ts`
+3. Add end-to-end tests for invalid payloads through the web UI forms.
+4. Add a small OpenAPI contract export from the Zod schemas so contractors and frontend work can share the same boundary definitions.
